<title>USA: Microsoft to hire 3,600 workers over next year.</title>
<headline>Microsoft to hire 3,600 workers over next year.</headline>
<dateline>REDMOND, Wash 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Microsoft plans to hire 3,600 people in the United States in the coming year, expanding its U.S. workforce by nearly 19 percent, company executives said.</p>
<p>Microsoft's chief operating officer, Robert Herbold, told reporters at a briefing the company added 2,529 workers in the fiscal year that ended on June 30, ending the year with slightly more than 22,000 workers worldwide.</p>
